headline: Lamb Weston Swings to Profit as Revenue Ticks Up
summary: Lamb Weston  swung to a profit in its latest quarter as revenue edged up.  The french-fry maker on Friday said it swung to a fiscal second-quarter profit of $62.1 million, or 44 cents a share, compared with a loss of $36.1 million, or 25 cents a share, a year earlier.  Adjusted earnings per share were 69 cents, ahead of estimates of 64 cents a share according to analysts polled by FactSet.

headline: Lamb Weston (NYSE:LW) Beats Q4 CY2025 Sales Expectations But Stock Drops
summary: Potato products company Lamb Weston (NYSE:LW) reported Q4 CY2025 results topping the market’s revenue expectations, with sales up 1.1% year on year to $1.62 billion. On the other hand, the company’s full-year revenue guidance of $6.45 billion at the midpoint came in 1% below analysts’ estimates. Its non-GAAP profit of $0.69 per share was 6.4% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
